Package: hyperspectR
Title: Hyperspectral Imaging Analysis for Biomedical Applications
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("R.", "Heller", email = "raban.heller@charite.de",
    role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8006-9742"))
Description: Read, process, analyze, and visualize hyperspectral imaging (HSI)
    data from Cubert snapshot cameras and standard ENVI/TIFF formats. Provides
    calibration workflows (dark correction, white reference normalization),
    spectral preprocessing (Savitzky-Golay smoothing, SNV, MSC, derivatives),
    biomedical tissue indices (tissue oxygenation StO2, perfusion NPI, hemoglobin
    THI, water content TWI), dimensionality reduction (PCA, MNF), pixel-wise
    classification (SAM, SVM, random forest), and spectral unmixing via
    Beer-Lambert chromophore fitting. Includes an interactive 'shiny' application
    for clinical hyperspectral image exploration. Designed for intraoperative
    imaging, soft tissue diagnostics, and perfusion monitoring workflows.
